-- Etisalat, Mobily Among 7 Firms to Build Middle East Fiber Optic Cable Line
-- B y   A y e s h a   D a y a
-- 2010-12-22T08:16:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-22/etisalat-mobily-among-7-firms-to-build-middle-east-cable-line.html
Emirates Telecommunications Corp. of
the United Arab Emirates and  Etihad Etisalat Co.  of Saudi Arabia
are among seven Middle Eastern telecoms operators that agreed to
build a fiber optic cable line from the U.A.E. to Turkey.  The Regional Cable Network will be operational in the
second-quarter of 2011 and requires an investment of about $500
million, Etisalat said in an e-mailed statement today. The
infrastructure has a data carrying capacity of 12.8 terabits a
second and will serve as a gateway to the Internet for 2 billion
people, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
